  "$comment": "Registry of UAE banks that publish credit-card Key Facts Statements (KFS). Drives the run.py orchestrator: for each bank with a known kfs_url, the named `extractor` adapter fetches and parses the KFS into normalized card records. The CBUAE Consumer Protection Regulation (2020) + Standards (2021) require every licensed bank to publish a per-card KFS in a semi-standardized format, which is what makes a single `generic_kfs` parser feasible across banks. kfs_source_type tells the router whether the document is a PDF or an HTML page. status 'verified' means the URL + source type were confirmed; 'to_verify' means the entry is a placeholder (kfs_url null) pending reconciliation. Foreign-bank retail footprints in the UAE shift (several wound down consumer cards); treat 'to_verify' rows as leads, not facts.",
  "note": "THIS LIST MUST BE RECONCILED AGAINST THE OFFICIAL CBUAE REGISTER OF LICENSED FINANCIAL INSTITUTIONS (https://www.centralbank.ae/en/our-operations/licensing-and-financial-institutions/) BEFORE ANY PRODUCTION USE. Bank legal names, KFS URLs, and which banks still issue consumer credit cards change; URLs here are best-known at as_of and several are intentionally null rather than invented. Always re-fetch the live KFS and human-verify before customer-facing output.",
